    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "I like the current way because it's namespaced. I hear the need for preventing the import of unnecessary stuff. Could we have a connector namespace?\n\n``` js\nimport {range} from 'react-instantsearch/connectors';\n// the connectors are in their own namespace to enforce using predictable naming\nimport {RangeInput} from 'react-instantsearch';\n// the default level is for connected components / widgets\nimport {RangeInputComponent} from 'react-instantsearch/component';\n// this namespace for the dumb components if we wish to expose them\n```\n",
