    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "@bobylito Yes this is a solution (namespacing connectors) that works. I am honestly hesitating between what you propose and this:\n\n``` js\nimport {RangeSlider, RangeInput, RangeConnector} from 'react-instantsearch';\n```\n\nBoth are very close but the above format does not require the user to add a new import line as soon as he wants to use SearchBox AND any connector, he can reuse the same single import:\n\n``` js\nimport {\n  SearchBox,\n  RangeConnector\n} from 'react-instantsearch';\n```\n\nWhat do you think?\n\n> import {RangeInputComponent} from 'react-instantsearch/component';\n> // this namespace for the dumb components if we wish to expose them\n\nSide note, I am not sure I understand what's the difference between RangeInput and RangeInputComponent. Today we only have RangeInput (our default, exposed, soon styled components)\n",
