  {
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Nice to restart this discussion\nWith what you propose @mthuret (and what I did propose at some point too) there are some flaws:\n- root level is DOM, making native look like not nice enough to be root (Thanks @bobylito for pointing that out in our discussion, took time but this makes sense now)\n- import {RangeInputComponent} from 'react-instantsearch/component'; is DOM only but you have no way to tell it. I am also unsure we need to expose them today? Where does the need comes from?\n\nIteration proposal:\n\n``` js\n// root level is kept for everything non platform specific, for now connectors mostly.\nimport {connectRange, connectSearchBox} from 'react-instantsearch';\nimport {RangeInput, InstantSearch} from 'react-instantsearch/dom';\nimport {InstantSearch} from 'react-instantsearch/native';\n```\n\nUltimately, we might even have to create different packages (for dom and native), just as facebook did (if we find the relevant reasons again).\n",
    "created_at": "2016-10-21T05:44:32Z",
